## Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project.

### Changes Made

**1. Package Installation:**
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1
- Added dependency to package.json
- Updated package-lock.json with new dependencies

**2. Code Integration:**
- Modified `app/layout.tsx` to integrate Analytics component
- Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"`
- Placed `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the `<Providers>` component
- Follows the official Next.js App Router pattern from Vercel documentation

**3. Implementation Details:**
- Framework: Next.js 16.2.2 with App Router
- Analytics component placed in the root layout for site-wide tracking
- Positioned after all content to avoid render blocking
- Used framework-specific import path: `@vercel/analytics/next`

**4. Verification:**
- TypeScript compilation: ✓ Passed
- Package installation: ✓ Successful
- Code structure: ✓ Preserved existing layout and styling
- Lock files: ✓ Updated

### Next Steps (Post-Deployment)

After deploying to Vercel:
1. Navigate to the Vercel dashboard Analytics section
2. Click "Enable" to activate Web Analytics
3. Deploy the application with `vercel deploy`
4. Analytics data will be available after several days of user traffic
5. Access analytics dashboard at `/_vercel/insights/*` routes

### Documentation Reference

Implementation based on official Vercel Analytics Quickstart guide:
https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart

The Analytics component will automatically collect visitor data once deployed to Vercel, with no additional configuration required.
